arity|PPP]], 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEOVN\"/>}}\n| gdp rank = {{plainlist|\n*[[List of countries by GDP (nominal)|44th (nominal, 2019)]] \n*[[List of countries by GDP (PPP)|32nd (PPP, 2019)]]}}\n| growth = {{plainlist|\n*7.1%&nbsp;(2018) 7.0%&nbsp;(2019e)\n*4.9%&nbsp;(2020B) 1.5%&nbsp;(2020LC)\n*7.5%&nbsp;(2021B) 4.0%&nbsp;(2021LC)<ref>{{cite web |title=World Bank East Asia and Pacific Economic Update, April 2020 : East Asia and Pacific in the Time of COVID-19 |url=https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/33477/9781464815652.pdf |website=openknowledge.worldbank.org |publisher=[[World Bank]] |accessdate=2 April 2020 |pages=20}}</ref>{{refn|group=note|Baseline (B) refers to a scenario of severe growth slowdown followed by a strong recovery. Lower case (LC) refers to a scenario of a deeper contraction followed by a sluggish recovery.}}}}\n| per capita = {{plainlist|\n*{{increase}} $2,740 (nominal, 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEOVN\"/>\n*{{increase}} $8,066 (PPP, 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEOVN\"/>}}\n| per capita rank = {{plainlist|\n*[[List of countries by GDP (nominal) per capita|130th (nominal, 2019)]] \n*[[List of countries by GDP (PPP) per capita|121st (PPP, 2018)]]}}\n| sectors = {{plainlist|\n*[[Primary sector of the economy|agriculture]]: 15.3%\n*[[Secondary sector of the economy|industry]]: 33.3%\n*[[Tertiary sector of the economy|services]]: 51% \n*(2017 est.)<ref name=\"cia2017\">[https://www.cia.gov/-library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/vm.html \"CIA World Factbook\"].</ref>}}\n| inflation = 3.8% (2020 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEOVN\"/>\n| poverty = {{plainlist|\n*6.7% (2018)<ref>{{cite web |title=Poverty headcount ratio at national poverty lines (% of population) - Vietnam |url=https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SI.POV.NAHC?locations=VN |website=data.worldbank.org |publisher=World Bank |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n*7.0% on less than $3.20/day (2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SI.POV.LMIC?locations=VN