{"title_page": "Easier (5 Seconds of Summer song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Easier\n| cover      = 5 Seconds of Summer - Easier.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[5 Seconds of Summer]]\n| album      = [[Calm (album)|Calm]]\n| released   = 23 May 2019\n| format     = \n*[[Music download|Digital download]]\n*[[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| length     = 2:37\n| recorded   = 2019\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Do NOT add any additional genres without providing reliable sources to back them up. If you do so, you will immediately be reverted and warned.-->*[[New wave music|New wave]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|title=Watch 5 Seconds of Summer's Gloomy Video for Nine Inch Nails-Inspired 'Easier'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/5-seconds-of-summer-easier-interview-new-song-837008/amp/|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=7 June 2019|date=23 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[electronic rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.udiscovermusic.com/news/watch-5-seconds-summers-video-easier/|title=discovermusic}}</ref>\n| label      = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     = \n*[[Louis Bell]]\n*[[Charlie Puth]]\n*[[Ali Tamposi]]\n*[[Ryan Tedder]]\n*[[Andrew Watt (musician)|Andrew Watt]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=ACE Repetory 'Easier' Work ID:897400286|url=https://www.ascap.com/repertory#ace/search/workID/897400286|website=[[ASCAP]]|accessdate=18 June 2019}}</ref>\n| producer   = \n*Charlie Puth\n*Louis Bell\n*Andrew Watt\n| prev_title = [[Who Do You Love (The Chainsmokers song)|Who Do You Love]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Teeth (5 Seconds of Summer song)|Teeth]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|b1dFSWLJ9wY|\"Easier\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Easier'''\" is a song by Australian [[pop rock]] band [[5 Seconds of Summer]]. The song was released on 23 May 2019 through [[Interscope Records]], as the lead single from their fourth studio album ''[[Calm (album)|Calm]]''. It is their first release on Interscope.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BxopF3LHr80/|title=5 Seconds of Summer on Instagram: \"EASIER // 05/23/2019\"|via=Instagram|accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine included the song on their 100 Best Songs of 2019 list at number 79.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8545893/best-songs-of-2019-top-100|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019: Staff List|authors=''Billboard'' Staff||date=December 11, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=December 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nBesides the original version, the band has also released an alternate version and two remixes of the song; on 5 July 2019, a version called \"Easier \u2013 Live from the Vault\" was released on YouTube with an accompanying music video. It was later made available on streaming services and for digital download as well.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/5-seconds-of-summer-easier-live-the-vault-5sos/|title=5 Seconds Of Summer enter the vault in moody \"Easier\" live performance|last=Campbell|first=Rachel|date=5 July 2019|website=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|language=en-US|accessdate= 16 March 2020}}</ref> On 12 July 2019, a remix by [[Seeb (music producers)|Seeb]] was released, and on 13 August 2019, a remix with [[Charlie Puth]] was released.<ref name=\"EasierRemix\" />\n\n==Promotion==\n5 Seconds of Summer posted clips on social media leading up to the announcement, posting teasers from the song's upcoming music video along with its name and release date.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jane|first=Karen|title=5 Seconds of Summer Might Be Dropping a New Song Called 'Easier'!|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/features/18765/5-seconds-of-summer-new-song-easier |website=[[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]|accessdate=19 May 2019|date=19 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'' described the song as \"dark\" and noted the inspiration from \"synth-heavy groups of the Eighties and Nineties like [[Depeche Mode]] and [[Tears for Fears]] and, more specifically, Nine Inch Nails' \"[[Closer (Nine Inch Nails song)|Closer]]\".<ref name=\"Gloomy\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/5-seconds-of-summer-easier-interview-new-song-837008/|title=Watch 5 Seconds of Summer's Gloomy Video for Nine Inch Nails-Inspired 'Easier'|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=23 May 2019|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|language=en-US|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' noted that \"the relatably heart-rending sentiment is elevated by lead singer Luke Hemmings' impassioned vocals, from the murmuring verses to the [[falsetto]] on the chorus\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8512884/5-seconds-of-summer-easier-video|title=5 Seconds Of Summer's 'Easier' Video: Watch|date=23 May 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video was released the same day as the single, 23 May 2019. It was directed by [[Grant Singer]].<ref name=\"Gloomy\" /> In the video, \"Hemmings, wearing a leather ensemble and glitter eyeshadow, sings chained by the wrists to the roof of a blue-lit cave while guitarist Michael Clifford, bassist Calum Hood and drummer Ashton Irwin rock out in front of the candle-studded backdrop [...] In addition to the cave setting, the video also features a striking seductress and haunting scenes of the bandmates submerged in on orange-lit pool and individually strolling down a long hallway in which their headshots are set ablaze.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2019/05/23/music-video-5-seconds-of-summer-easier/|title=Check out the edgy music video for new 5 Seconds of Summer single, 'Easier'|website=[[Entertainment Weekly|EW]]|language=EN|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe blue lighting prominent throughout the video follows the aesthetic of the single's artwork. 4 symbols, representing each member, which were used in the teasers for the song, were also featured in the video as tattoos along the female dancer's spine as well as on a burning poster by the end.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewhisp.mommyish.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/symbols-5-seconds-of-summer-video-easier-era-meaning/|title=5 Seconds Of Summer's New Music Video Just Dropped & Everyone's Wondering The Same Thing|date=23 May 2019|website=the whisp|language=en-US|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of March 2020, the video has over 44 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b1dFSWLJ9wY|title=5 Seconds of Summer - Easier|accessdate=13 March 2020|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download\n| title1 = Easier\n| length1 = 2:37\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=\"SeeB\"/>\n| title1 = Easier\n| note1 = [[SeeB]] Remix\n| length1 = 2:45\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=\"LFTV\"/>\n| title1 = Easier\n| note1 = Live from The Vault\n| length1 = 3:26\n}}\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|12|artist=5 Seconds of Summer|song=Easier|rowheader=true|accessdate=1 June 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|58|artist=5 Seconds of Summer|song=Easier|rowheader=true|accessdate=5 June 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|48|artist=5 Seconds of Summer|song=Easier|rowheader=true|accessdate=14 June 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|37|artist=5 Seconds of Summer|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 June 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| China Airplay/FL (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboardchina.cn/top/radiocharts/2019-07-08.html|title=China Airplay Chart/Foreign Language - 08/07